data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_f4de3e07a7325ae60069a9f1f8b820819095cabb83fafda81d","logprobs":[],"output_index":2,"sequence_number":218,"text":"**Most recent story (from “What’s new today”)**\n\n- **Title:** *Defending the gates: How a global coalition disrupted Tycoon 2FA, a major driver of initial access and large-scale online impersonation*  \n- **Date:** Mar 4, 2026  \n- **Link:** https://blogs.microsoft.com/on-the-issues/2026/03/04/how-a-global-coalition-disrupted-tycoon/\n\n**Summary:**  \nMicrosoft reports on an international effort to disrupt “Tycoon 2FA,” a phishing-as-a-service operation used to steal credentials and bypass multi-factor authentication at scale. The story explains how the service enabled widespread account takeovers and impersonation affecting multiple sectors (including education and healthcare). Microsoft, Europol, and other partners coordinated actions such as seizing hundreds of domains and targeting supporting infrastructure to reduce the operation’s ability to deliver phishing and facilitate cybercrime, underscoring the importance of ongoing public-private collaboration against identity-based attacks."}

